<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-09-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-09-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="579" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d579">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Porter</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-09-19"><hi rend="italic">September 19,
                                    1900</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 835.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            dispatch No. 725, of the 28th ultimo, relative to the loss of the French
                            torpedo-boat destroyer <hi rend="italic">Framée</hi>, and to inform you
                            in reply that the Department approves your course in expressing the
                            sympathy of your embassy to the French Government.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">David J. Hill</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>